author: Warhammer
description:
On hallowed ground sits a Necromancer’s dream – three Cursed Sepulchres, spewing out all the deathly energies one could want. But they need painting up to really get the dead moving, and we have three different schemes to try.

Here’s a list of the paints we used in today’s video:

Base 
Abaddon Black 
Corvus Black
Ionrach Skin
Iron Warriors
Rhinox Hide
Waaagh! Flesh

Layer 
Administratum Grey 
Fulgrim Pink
Gauss Blaster Green
Ironbreaker
Screaming Skull
Stormhost Silver
Sybarite Green
Ulthuan Grey

Contrast
Aeldari Emerald 
Flesh Tearers Red
Luxion Purple
Magos Purple
Militarum Green
Skeleton Horde

Shade
Agrax Earthshade
Nuln Oil
Mortarion Grime 

Technicals
Contrast Medium
Nihilakh Oxide
Lahmian Medium

If you're new to painting, our Colour Painting Essentials playlist hosts an array of beginner-friendly videos to help you get started.

title: Three Ways To Paint Spooky Graves | Warhammer Age of Sigmar
